<p>The <b>hoopoe</b> <span class="nowrap"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English" title="Help:IPA for English">/</a></span><span class="IPA nopopups"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key" title="Help:IPA for English"><span title="/ˈ/ primary stress follows" style="border-bottom:1px dotted">ˈ</span></a></span><span class="IPA nopopups"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key" title="Help:IPA for English"><span title="'h' in 'hi'" style="border-bottom:1px dotted">h</span></a></span><span class="IPA nopopups"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key" title="Help:IPA for English"><span title="/uː/ long 'oo' in 'food'" style="border-bottom:1px dotted">uː</span></a></span><span class="IPA nopopups"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key" title="Help:IPA for English"><span title="'p' in 'pie'" style="border-bottom:1px dotted">p</span></a></span><span class="IPA nopopups"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English#Key" title="Help:IPA for English"><span title="/uː/ long 'oo' in 'food'" style="border-bottom:1px dotted">uː</span></a></span><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:IPA_for_English" title="Help:IPA for English">/</a></span></span> (<i>Upupa epops</i>) is a colourful bird found across <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Afro-Eurasia" title="Afro-Eurasia">Afro-Eurasia</a>, notable for its distinctive "crown" of feathers. It is the only <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Extant_taxon" title="Extant taxon">extant</a> species in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Family_(biology)" title="Family (biology)">family</a> <b>Upupidae</b>. One insular species, the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Saint_Helena_hoopoe" title="Saint Helena hoopoe">Saint Helena hoopoe</a>, is extinct, and the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Madagascan_hoopoe" title="Madagascan hoopoe">Madagascar subspecies</a> of the hoopoe is sometimes elevated to a full species. Like the Latin name <i>upupa</i>, the English name is an <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Onomatopoetic" title="Onomatopoetic" class="mw-redirect">onomatopoeic</a> form which imitates the cry of the bird. The hoopoe is the national bird of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Israel" title="Israel">Israel</a>.</p>
<p></p>
